  "body": "Address this todo:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/2de4562983b4af39cdb9c2340be04ef9f387b51c/plugin/pkg/admission/security/podsecuritypolicy/admission.go#L334-L340\r\n\r\nWhich is supported by the latest [scale testing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IIcHHE_No1KMAybW5krIphdN325eGa2sxF2eqg2YAPI/edit#heading=h.jb1b0ho51ka6)\r\n\r\nNote that the pod create latency is still impacted by policies that are not bound, probably since every policy is checked for authorization twice (creator account & pod service account). It may be more efficient to look for a policy that permits the pod, and only check authorization on success (especially when authorization includes a webhook).\r\n\r\n/cc @kubernetes/sig-auth-bugs @kubernetes/sig-scalability-bugs @liggitt @pweil- ",
